Others: Immanuel Quickley scored 21 points and made 15 assists after missing the Raptors' last 22 games with a partially torn ulnar collateral ligament in his right elbow.
Quickley made a 29-foot three-pointer to cap a 25-6 Raptors run in the fourth quarter as Toronto beat the Brooklyn Nets 130-113 on Wednesday to snap an 11-game losing skid.
Quickley averaged 18.6 points, 6.8 assists, and 4.8 rebounds — all career highs — in 38 games for Toronto last season after being traded to the Raptors by the New York Knicks on Dec. 30, 2023.
Quickley signed a five-year, US$175-million contract with the Raptors in July.
Head coach Darko Rajakovic praised Quickley's skills and ability to call plays on the run.
Scottie Barnes led all scorers with 33 points and 13 rebounds.
RJ Barrett, who averages 30 points at home, is expected to improve the team's overall performance.
Jakob Poeltl and Gradey Dick are also part of the starting lineup if or when they are all healthy.
